Stile Notes & DNA Diagram

Evolution stile notes:

Definition of Evolution: Evolution is change in the heritable characteristics of biological populations over successive generations. These characteristics are the expressions of genes that are passed on from parent to offspring during reproduction. All species have gone through evolution at some point for an example the on sources shows how native birds went through evolution.
DOC

Genetics stile notes:

DNA are molecules carrying genetic instructions for the development, functioning, growth and reproduction of all known organisms and many viruses, DNA is made up of genes and said genes give instructions to the body on how to make specific traits/proteins. DNA is also known as "Double-Helix" (DNA is made of two linked strands that wind around each other to resemble a twisted ladder)
